  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Adjust Gallery Card Layout to Overlay Card Count on Image\n\nFix the gallery card layout so that the card-count element overlays the image instead of appearing below it.\n\nRequirements:\n- Remove aspect-ratio CSS property from .gallery-card .gallery-card-image element\n- OR implement alternative CSS solution to enable overlay positioning\n- Ensure card-count element is positioned over the image (typically using absolute positioning)\n- Verify the overlay appears in the intended position (e.g., top-right, bottom-right corner)\n- Maintain image responsiveness and proper display across different screen sizes\n- Test that overlay remains visible with appropriate z-index and contrast\n\nTechnical considerations:\n- Parent container may need position: relative for absolute positioning to work\n- Consider adding semi-transparent background to card-count for readability\n- Ensure overlay doesn't break existing hover states or interactions",
